Skull is delicate, with rostrum rather short and eyes rather large, giving a juvenile appearance (
Fig. 7A
). Nasals not extending beyond premaxillary-frontal suture (
Fig. 6A
). Incisive foramina short, the posterior margin just reaching M1 (
Fig. 6B
). Palate long, extending beyond the posterior plane of M3. Posterolateral palatal pits anterior to mesopterygoid fossa. Small bullae not very inflated, with eustachian tubes short, not reaching the posterior edge of parapterygoid processes.

Upper incisors opistodont, ungrooved, and pigmented orange in front. Maxillary toothrows slightly posteriorly convergent. Primary cusps of molars alternate. M1 with anteriomedian flexus absent (
Fig. 6I
). M2 with hypoflexus and metaflexus open and lophs and styles absent. M3 with hypoflexus present. m1 with well-developed procingulum; m2 with anterolophid absent; m3 with hypoflexid present.
